properties.areaDesc: Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 4 at 12:29PM MST until February 5 at 1:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...STRONG GUSTY WINDS WILL RETURN TO THE SOUTHWEST PLATTE COUNTY
LATE TONIGHT ALONG WITH PERIODS OF BLOWING SNOW...

* WHAT...West winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 55 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
County.

* WHEN...From 2 AM to 1 PM MST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property
and cause power outages. Travel will be difficult especially
for lightweight, high profile vehicles and campers.
properties.instruction:
People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown
around or damaged by the wind.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 2 AM TO 1 PM MST WEDNESDAY
